f
(-1,\infty)
f(0)=1
x\geq 0
f'(x)+f(x)-\frac{1}{x+1}\int_0^x f(t)dt =0,
e^{-x}\leq f(x)\leq 1.
f(x)\geq e^{-x}
f\leq 1
f'(x)-\frac{1}{x+1}\int_0^x f(t)dt =-f(x)\leq -e^{-x},
f(x)-f(0)-\int_0^x \frac{1}{t+1}\int_0^t f(s)dsdt\leq e^{-x}-1
f(x)\leq e^{-x}+\int_0^x f(s)[\ln (x+1)-\ln(s+1)]ds.
0<f(x)\leq g(x)+\int_0^x h(t)f(t)dt\Rightarrow f(x)\leq g(x)+\int_0^x h(s)g(s)e^{\int_s^x h(t)dt}ds
